<html><head><meta name="color-scheme" content="light dark"><meta charset="utf-8"></head><body><pre>{"id":1537,"date":"2024-07-31T23:55:00","date_gmt":"2024-07-31T13:55:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/?p=1537"},"modified":"2024-08-01T11:04:25","modified_gmt":"2024-08-01T01:04:25","slug":"defend-the-cfmeu","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/defend-the-cfmeu\/","title":{"rendered":"Defend the CFMEU"},"content":{"rendered":"\n&lt;p&gt;The attacks on the CFMEU have more to do with the interests of capital than any organised crime within the union.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The capitalist media in Australia have launched a massive propaganda attack on the Construction &amp;amp; General Division of the Construction, Forestry &amp;amp; Maritime Employees Union (CFMEU). Though initiated by Nine Entertainment, the battle has been joined by all organs of the media, from the ABC to the Murdoch gutter press. The capitalist class sees an opportunity to smash the strongest union in the country and drive down wages for the best paid section of the working class, with inevitable flow on effects for all workers. This is class war.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;Grainy footage leaked by the cops and a handful of workplace delegates who are former bikies have been woven up to create a story of a thoroughly corrupt union. We\u2019ll be honest \u2013 there are corrupt union officials, and they should be disposed of. Any official who takes a bribe should have a black mark against their name for eternity. But the attacks on the CFMEU are not about union corruption, they are about breaking the wages and conditions of construction workers. Governments have been happy to let developers rip vast sums off buyers in high-rise residential towers that were never fit for habitation and allow standover merchants to settle disputes between contractors, so they can\u2019t be believed when they say they want to root corruption out of the CFMEU.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;It is the job of members to organise against corruption in the union movement and root it out. \u201cUnions\u201d like Shop Distributive and Allied (the SDA) routinely collude with big business to hold down the wages of retail and fast food workers.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The Australian Workers Union (AWU) undermines wages and safety in civil construction, cleaning, road works and more. The ACTU and ALP affiliated unions routinely put the electoral interests of the ALP ahead of workers.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The CFMEU\u2019s real crime is that they have achieved a de facto closed shop over the state government\u2019s \u201cBig Build\u201d and much of the city\u2019s high rise development. In theory, the AWU have coverage over civil construction, but the CFMEU drove them out by delivering much better wages and conditions. This is a good thing. ACTU coverage rules allow Australia\u2019s Worst Union to operate by undercutting wages and safety conditions in order to get preferential treatment from the bosses. When the capitalist press says \u201cwe all pay\u201d for the CFMEU, what they mean is that construction workers wages should be lower.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div class=\"wp-block-image\"&gt;\n&lt;figure class=\"aligncenter size-medium\"&gt;&lt;img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" src=\"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/37685239966_0deace1e88_c-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"CFMEU flag flying with the Eureka Stockade Flag, next to a construction crane. \" class=\"wp-image-1545\" srcset=\"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/37685239966_0deace1e88_c-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/37685239966_0deace1e88_c-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/37685239966_0deace1e88_c.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/&gt;&lt;figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"&gt;Image by Leonard J Matthews&lt;\/figcaption&gt;&lt;\/figure&gt;\n&lt;\/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The last Liberal government launched a Royal Commission into Trade Union Corruption, targeted squarely at the CFMEU. No substantive prosecutions resulted. They re-established the Australian Building and Construction Commission (ABCC), tasked with fining the CFMEU out of existence. They did not succeed. They passed laws to enable the Fair Work Commission to place unions into administration, but they didn\u2019t dare use them.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The Labor government, ever keen to demonstrate their reliability to capital, has now moved to crush the CFMEU. In less than a week, Albanese has moved to do what the Liberals never could.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The Federal Labor government has asked the Fair Work Commission to apply to the Federal Court to place branches of the CFMEU into external administration. An administrator would be able to act as the union, taking over its assets, firing union staff, purging members, removing delegates, and ousting officials.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;But the real prize of administration is the ability to rip up Enterprise Agreements (EBAs). Labor have made clear they are prepared to pass special legislation to give any administrator \u201cfull powers\u201d to \u201cact in the public interest\u201d. An administrator appointed by the Fair Work Commission, acting as the union, will have little trouble applying to the Commission to terminate union agreements and drive union members down to the award (industry specific minimum pay and conditions) \u2013 which, in construction, is vastly below industry standards.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;Government administration of a union is an affront to the very concept of unionism. Workers build unions in order to build their collective strength, and coordinate their collective action. We fight to defend unions as organisations built by workers, consisting of workers, and democratically controlled by workers. In the face of union corruption, we have to organise and overthrow corrupt or self interested officials. The only people who should be \u201ccleaning the house\u201d are union members.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The ALP is historically a party of the trade union bureaucracy. Through the ALP, the trade union bureaucracy attempts to negotiate a compromise with capital on the overall management of capitalism in Australia. In 2021-2024 the CFMEU gave $4.3 million to the ALP, stumping up a sizeable portion of the funding to get Anthony Albanese elected. Albanese and the ALP are now moving to destroy the CFMEU. There is a lesson in this. The interests of individual union leadership (let alone any group of workers) will always come second to the collective interest the ALP has in perpetuating its own position as a party of government within Australian capitalism.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The treacherous nature of the trade union bureaucracy can be seen in the actions of the ACTU. Faced with a frontal assault on the principles of trade unionism, Sally McManus and the ACTU executive demanded that \u201cthe leadership of the CFMEU \u2026 support the appointment of an independent and external administrator and to cooperate with such an administration\u201d. CFMEU representatives on ACTU executive were not even permitted to argue against the motion!&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;Far from supporting a government administrator, the members of the CFMEU should fight it with every tool at their disposal and call on their officials to follow them. There should be a campaign of complete non-cooperation with any government appointed administrator. The hard won pay, conditions and strength of tens of thousands of construction workers is at stake today and that of the rest of us tomorrow.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;Sally McManus said she could count the unions opposing the CFMEU\u2019s suspension on one hand. It\u2019s up to the rank and file of every union to make sure that number grows. Members of every union must organise in solidarity with construction workers and their union.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;Shop Stewards (delegates) on every site and in every state should establish committees for member control of the union. The moment any administrator is appointed, these committees should simply act as the union. Officials and employees of the CFMEU Construction and General Division should recognise these committees and take direction from them. As part of this, CFMEU officials and elected leaders should hand over all readily available resources (especially contact lists) to such committees before administration comes into effect, and in defiance of the law once it is in effect.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The Shop Stewards committees should begin immediate work to organise resistance against administration and to defend EBAs and coverage, in particular on all Big Build projects. As soon as administration is in effect, members should organise to divert payment of all union dues to those committees.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;The governments\u2019 attacks on the CFMEU can be defeated. The CFMEU must be defended. It is essential that all union members fight to defend the principle of independent trade unions under member control.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;An attack on one union is an attack on all unions, and an attack on unions is an attack on all workers.&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;p class=\"has-text-align-center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Touch one, Touch all&lt;\/strong&gt;&lt;\/p&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div class=\"wp-block-image\"&gt;\n&lt;figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"&gt;&lt;img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/Sam-Wallman-CFMEU-1024x1024.jpg\" alt=\"Cartoon of city with text &amp;quot;We Built This City&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Defend the CFMEU&amp;quot;. \" class=\"wp-image-1543\" srcset=\"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/Sam-Wallman-CFMEU-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/Sam-Wallman-CFMEU-300x300.jpg 300w, https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/Sam-Wallman-CFMEU-150x150.jpg 150w, https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/Sam-Wallman-CFMEU-768x769.jpg 768w, https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/Sam-Wallman-CFMEU-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/07\/Sam-Wallman-CFMEU.jpg 2046w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/&gt;&lt;figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"&gt;Image by Sam Wallman&lt;\/figcaption&gt;&lt;\/figure&gt;\n&lt;\/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;\/p&gt;\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"The attacks on the CFMEU have more to do with the interests of capital than any organised crime within the union.\n&lt;a class=\"moretag\" href=\"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/defend-the-cfmeu\/\"&gt; [...]&lt;\/a&gt;","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1541,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_coblocks_attr":"","_coblocks_dimensions":"","_coblocks_responsive_height":"","_coblocks_accordion_ie_support":"","footnotes":""},"categories":[2,28],"tags":[66,46],"class_list":["post-1537","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-anvil","category-workers","tag-cfmeu","tag-unions"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1537","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1537"}],"version-history":[{"count":7,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1537\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1572,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1537\/revisions\/1572"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/1541"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1537"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=1537"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/melbacg.au\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=1537"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}</pre><div class="json-formatter-container"></div></body></html>